  "content": " dimension for the 1.200mm x 800mm footprint can be found in the following attachment: EA-SC (Significant/Special Characteristic)-xx-M-001-A-01. The corrugated material must have minimum 44 ECT (Edge Crush Test) to provide a sufficient strength in order to maintain part quality. Minimum BCT (Box Compression Test) requirement is explained in section 4.2.9. The flute direction shall be vertical to optimize the compression strength. All carton boxes shall be adequately sealed with packaging tape. Staples as well as asphalt sealing tapes are not allowed. Hand holes should not be used, unless specified by YAZAKI . Template: EA-QM-xx-P-001-F-01 Rev1.0 27/APR/2017 Print Date: 15/MAY/2023 Revision Date: Europe Business Management System 15/MAY/2023 EA-SC (Significant/Special Characteristic)-xx-M-001 Revision Level: Supplier  Logistics Manual MANUAL REV 1.1 CONFIDENTIAL: This information is Yazaki (Yazaki EMEA) property and must follow applicable global and regional confidentiality rules. Copies are reference only, see network for latest revision. 4.2.3 Ergonomic Requirements & Container Utilization The weight per manually handled handling unit is limited to 15kg. In case local legal requirements imposes a lower weight limit, the legal requirements must be always respected. Each handling unit shall reach a minimum vertical box density of 90% based on the following formula: Height of goods in container vertical box density (%) = Height of container 4.2.4 Expendable (One-way, apply to carton/container box) Packaging Corrugated box material as well as the used internal dunnage shall be 100% recyclable. During the design of the box and dunnage the loading, unloading, recycling, and disposal shall be considered. All the boxes shall be regular slotted container (RSC (Regular Slotted Container (e.g. FEFCO 0201))) with flaps for closure. Half slotted container (HSC (Half Slotted Container (e.g. FEFCO 0312))) shall not be used. Figure 1 Authorized carton box types 4.2.5 Returnable Packaging In case of mutually agreed use of returnable packaging, the ownership as well as the responsibilities for maintenance, repair, cleaning, tracking, etc. shall be determined during the sourcing process. Rental of returnable packaging may also be pursued as an option. For standard parts, the returnable packaging shall conform to the VDA (Verband der Automobilindustrie (German Automotive Association)) or Odette GALIA packaging standards. Template: EA-QM-xx-P-001-F-01 Rev1.0 27/APR/201"
}


